name: NPGA single stall washroom
directions: Upon entrance there is a desk, to the left is a hallway with gendered stalled washrooms, before ten to the immediate left is a staircase. Go up the stair case and through the door to the viewing area that is on the left. To the left again, are a couple gender neutral single stall washrooms.
comment: Since it's in the viewing area, you shouldn't have any trouble. If someone questions you, the staff is nice and will probably let you use them if you say you needed to use a gender neutral washroom and knew of this one.

name: Airport single stall washroom
directions: If going through the departure door, take an immediate left and it's the second door on the left side wall. If arriving at airport, it's on the left down the hall towards the departures. Go past the cafeteria, past the security desk, and then past the gendered washrooms. It will be on the right.

name: NLC single stall washroom
directions: When the college campus is open, enter the main doors with the front desk, go straight until you're in the cafeteria to the right. On the right side of the kitchen are two gendered washrooms and further right is a hallway. Go down the hallway about 3/4 of the way and there is a gender neutral bathroom.

name: The Burrow
directions: It is to the left in the ground floor of the cafe, with clear signage.
comment: The Burrow is an easygoing, progressive cafe and community hotspot in West End, with three accessible toilets adjoining an open washroom. You do not have to purchase from the cafe to utilise the bathroom.

name: Bryce

name: Cafe

name: Broomfield Public Library
directions: After entering the building, go right to enter the library. There are 2 unisex restrooms on the first floor, with an additional one within the Children's Library (toilet and sink are child-height). Upstairs, accessible by elevator or stairs, there are 2 more unisex restrooms toward the back of the library past the meeting rooms.
comment: All 5 restrooms within the library are unisex single-stall and available whenever the library is open. For hours, go to www.broomfieldlibrary.org. (Note: The lobby area has only gendered, multi-stall restrooms, so please enter the library for the individual unisex ones.)

name: Birmingham City University City South Campus

Accessibility is limited because the cubicles are slightly small, but they're still larger than typical cubicles.
comment: Need to have BCU student ID to get in through the main entrance.
